It comes as reports came to light that Prince Charles and Camilla are in talks with the BBC to host the show inside the royal residence. The Duke and Duchess of Cornwall are thought to be superfans of the show, while sources told the Sun that the Queen has already given her blessing for the episode to be filmed inside the Palace. Commenting on the news, royal expert Richard Eden wrote on Twitter that “perhaps Prince Harry and Meghan could be invited to be contestants” in the show. The couple caused a stir among fans when they returned to the UK for the Platinum Jubilee celebrations last week, after two years since they stepped down from senior members of the Firm and moved to the US. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...